<h1>Job&nbsp;Description</h1><p>Safety Ambassadors are a uniformed patrol who act as a positive, friendly, and welcoming presence in the <a href="http://downtownwilmingtonde.com/bid">BID</a>. They work in partnership with the police, provide information about attractions, give directions, serve as safety escorts, check on parking lots and garages, interact with visitors, and check in on businesses in the neighborhood. Safety Ambassadors also often support <a href="http://downtownwilmingtonde.com/annual-events">events</a>. Ambassadors work on a rotating schedule consisting of a day shift (from 8:00 a.m. to 4:00 pm.) and a night shift (from 4:00 p.m. to midnight), including some weekends and holidays.</p><h1>What We Offer</h1><p>We offer full-time (40 hours) employment on a year-round basis. Our benefits include: medical and dental insurance, paid vacation, personal time, sick time, and a retirement savings plan. Uniforms are provided, cleaned and maintained free of charge.</p><h1>Requirements</h1><p>Must be at least 18 years of age and a high school graduate or GED. Mandatory pre-employment testing including: controlled substance screening, criminal background investigation and reference check. Applications will not be accepted from anyone convicted of felonies, thefts, assaults or any drug-related offense. Downtown Visions also reserves the right to perform random drug testing.</p><h1>Apply</h1><p>If you would like to become part of the Downtown Visions team, please send an e-mail to:</p><p>Michael Maggitti<br />Director of Operations<br />mmaggitti@downtownvisions.org</p><p>Applications will be sent via e-mail. Downtown Visions is an EEO employer. No phone calls please.</p>]]></content:encoded></item><item><title>Job Opportunity: Cleaning Ambassador</title><dc:creator>Sarah Zero</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 04 Aug 2015 11:49:14 +0000</pubDate><link>http://downtownwilmingtonde.com/jobs-blog/2015/8/4/3hef0ad6mbm1c7bnip4klw271skpsl</link><guid isPermaLink="false">5515b9d