<h1>Job Description</h1><p>Cleaning Ambassadors are uniformed personnel who act as a positive, friendly and welcoming presence in the <a href="http://downtownwilmingtonde.com/bid">BID</a>. They remove litter, graffiti, illegal posters, as well as weeds and leaves&nbsp;to ensure cleanliness and safety. Cleaning Ambassadors&nbsp;also do seasonal pressure washing. Ambassadors work four 10-hour days; providing&nbsp;our services seven days a week from 7 a.m. to 5 p.m.</p><h1>What We Offer</h1><p>We offer full-time (40 hours) employment on a year-round basis. Our benefits include: medical and dental insurance, paid vacation, personal time, sick time, and a retirement savings plan. Uniforms are provided, cleaned and maintained free of charge.</p><h1>Requirements</h1><p>Must be at least 18 years of age and a high school graduate or GED. Mandatory pre-employment testing including: controlled substance screening, criminal background investigation and reference check. Applications will not be accepted from anyone convicted of felonies, thefts, assaults or any drug-related offense. Downtown Visions also reserves the right to perform random drug testing.</p><h1>Apply</h1><p>If you would like to become part of the Downtown Visions team, please send an e-mail to:</p><p>Michael Maggitti<br />Director of Operations<br />mmaggitti@downtownvisions.org</p><p>Applications will be sent via e-mail. Downtown Visions is an EEO employer. No phone calls please.</p>]]></content:encoded></item></channel></rss>